<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-13T02:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-13T02:16:00-05:00" n="631" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d631">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">394.115 Panay/7: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Naval Attaché in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bemis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of Naval Operations</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi></persName>)<note n="61" xml:id="d631fn61">Copy transmitted to the Department by the Navy
                                Department.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-13T16:16:00+09:00">December 13, 1937—4:16
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 13—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1613. Senior Aide to Navy Minister called today to inform Naval Attaché
                            of sinking of U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Panay</hi> by Japenese bombing
                            planes and stated: “Navy Minister wishes to express to Secretary of Navy
                            and U. S. Navy his sincerest regret to this unhappy accident.[”]</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>